              "name": "message",
              "value": "=This email was sent on: {{ $json.d.createdTimestamp ?? $json.d.createdDate ?? $now.toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd') }}. Use this date as the reference point when resolving relative dates like \"tomorrow\", \"next week\", \"this Friday\", etc.. Here is the raw HTML content of a school news item:\n{{ $json.d.itemContent }}                                                                                                                                                                                           Analyze this content carefully.\n1. Determine if it is relevant to my daughter Diana in Grade 2 (e.g., mentions \"Grade 2\", \"Year 2\", \"Diana\", or is a whole-school announcement).\n2. Extract ALL concrete scheduled events or action deadlines from the text.\n       - Relative dates like \"tomorrow\", \"next Monday\", \"this Friday\" ARE concrete — resolve them using today's date above.\n       - Explicit times like \"9:10am\", \"2:30pm\" ARE concrete.\n       - Do NOT create events for general, open-ended requests with no identifiable date or time (e.g., \"help when you can\", \"book covering tubs available\").\n       - If the text mentions multiple times for the same day (e.g., an event start and an early dismissal), use the earliest time as \"start_time\" and the latest time as \"end_time\".\n       - For \"end_time\": if an explicit end time, dismissal time, or pickup time is mentioned, use it. If no end time can be determined, set \"end_time\" to 2 hours after \"start_time\".\n       - \"end_time\" must NEVER be null if \"start_time\" is set.\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object of the following format, and nothing else:                   \n{                    \n\"involved\": true/false,                  \n\"has_deadline_or_event\": true/false,                  \n\"title\": \"Name of the event / deadline (or null if none)\",                  \n\"start_time\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS (or null if none)\",                  \n\"end_time\": \"YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS (or null if none)\",                  \n\"summary\": \"Brief summary of the details\"                  \n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "system_prompt",
              "value": "You are a parent's assistant analyzing school notifications. You MUST respond ONLY with a raw JSON block matching the requested format. "
            },
